description:
## What
Add JSON-RPC 2.0 envelope types, typed param/result structs, method string constants, and error code constants to core/src/protocol.rs. No removal of RelayMessage yet — that happens once W1A+W1B both remove their last RelayMessage uses.

## Algorithm
1. Add four envelope structs with serde derives (all #[serde(rename_all = "snake_case")] where appropriate):
   - JsonRpcRequest { #[serde(rename="jsonrpc")] version: String, id: u64, method: String, params: Option<serde_json::Value> }
   - JsonRpcNotification { #[serde(rename="jsonrpc")] version: String, method: String, params: Option<serde_json::Value> }
   - JsonRpcResponse { #[serde(rename="jsonrpc")] version: String, id: u64, result: Option<serde_json::Value>, error: Option<JsonRpcError> }
   - JsonRpcError { code: i32, message: String, #[serde(skip_serializing_if="Option::is_none")] data: Option<serde_json::Value> }
   All Option fields use #[serde(skip_serializing_if="Option::is_none")]
2. Add helper methods on JsonRpcResponse:
   - pub fn success(id: u64, result: impl Serialize) -> Result<Self, serde_json::Error>
   - pub fn error(id: u64, code: i32, message: impl Into<String>) -> Self
   - pub fn is_success(&self) -> bool  (result is Some, error is None)
3. Add helper methods on JsonRpcNotification:
   - pub fn new(method: impl Into<String>, params: impl Serialize) -> Result<Self, serde_json::Error>
4. Add pub mod rpc_methods with string constants:
   CHALLENGE, AUTHENTICATE, BROADCAST, DELIVER, DIRECTORY_LIST,
   USER_JOINED, USER_LEFT, SET_NICKNAME, USER_NICKNAME,
   SUBSCRIBE_REQUEST, SUBSCRIPTION_ACTIVE,
   PUBLISH_KEY_PACKAGE, GET_KEY_PACKAGE, KEY_PACKAGE_RESPONSE, KEY_PACKAGE_READY,
   WHISPER, WHISPER_DELIVER
5. Add pub mod rpc_errors with i32 constants:
   PARSE_ERROR=-32700, INVALID_REQUEST=-32600, METHOD_NOT_FOUND=-32601,
   AUTH_FAILED=-32001, NOT_AUTHENTICATED=-32002, SPOOFED_SENDER=-32003, NICKNAME_TAKEN=-32004
6. Add typed param/result structs for each method (pub, #[derive(Debug,Clone,Serialize,Deserialize)]):
   - ChallengeParams { nonce: String }
   - AuthenticateParams { pub_key: String, nonce: String, signature: String }
   - AuthenticateResult { pub_id: String, subscription_expires: Option<String> }
   - BroadcastParams { #[serde_as(as="Base64")] payload: Vec<u8> }
   - BroadcastResult { message_id: String }
   - DeliverParams { from: String, #[serde_as(as="Base64")] payload: Vec<u8> }
   - SetNicknameParams { nickname: String }
   - GetKeyPackageParams { pub_id: String }
   - GetKeyPackageResult { pub_id: String, #[serde_as(as="Option<Base64>")] data: Option<Vec<u8>> }
   - PublishKeyPackageParams { #[serde_as(as="Base64")] data: Vec<u8> }
   - KeyPackageReadyParams { pub_id: String }
   - WhisperParams { to: String, #[serde_as(as="Base64")] payload: Vec<u8> }
   - WhisperDeliverParams { from: String, #[serde_as(as="Base64")] payload: Vec<u8> }
   - UserJoinedParams { pub_id: String, nickname: Option<String>, sequence: u64 }
   - UserLeftParams { pub_id: String }
   - UserNicknameParams { pub_id: String, nickname: String }
   - DirectoryListParams { online: Vec<UserInfo>, offline: Vec<UserInfo> }
   - SubscriptionActiveParams { expires: String }

## Defensive programming rules
- All serde optional fields use skip_serializing_if not default
- The 'jsonrpc' field literal must match JSON-RPC 2.0 spec exactly
- No unwrap in helper methods — return Result where fallible
- method string constants must match exact lowercase names in the epic spec

## Agent team: Standard (R + I + T)
- R: Read core/src/protocol.rs to understand existing structure, confirm serde_with usage pattern
- I: Add the new types and constants to protocol.rs
- T: Write tests that assert exact JSON-RPC 2.0 wire format for each envelope type (spec string matching, NOT roundtrip-only)

## Tests (all with external oracle: JSON-RPC 2.0 spec)
- request_serializes_to_spec_format: assert serialized == '{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":1,"method":"authenticate","params":{"nonce":"abc","pub_key":"xyz","signature":"sig"}}'
- notification_has_no_id: assert serialized JsonRpcNotification does not contain '"id"'
- response_success_format: assert serialized JsonRpcResponse with result contains '"result"' and does not contain '"error"'
- response_error_format: assert serialized JsonRpcResponse with error contains '"error"' code and does not contain '"result"'
- error_data_omitted_when_none: assert JsonRpcError with data=None does not serialize '"data"'
- authenticate_params_base64_roundtrip: BroadcastParams with random bytes serializes payload as base64 string, not array
